description:
The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the FTSE Emerging Comprehensive Factor Index.
 The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets (but typically far more) in component securities (including depositary receipts in respect of such securities) of the underlying index. The index is designed to track the equity market performance of companies in emerging market countries selected on the investment style criteria of value, momentum, quality, low volatility and size. The fund is non-diversified.
